According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Elderly Care Service Platform Market was valued at USD 653 million in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 1.275 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 10.3% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing robust growth due to the rapidly aging global population, increasing adoption of digital healthcare solutions, expanding home-based elderly care services, and growing government support for integrated care platforms.
Elderly care service platforms are transforming senior healthcare by integrating home-based care, institutional care, community services, and medical support into a single digital ecosystem. Through mobile applications, web platforms, hotlines, and offline service centers, these platforms provide one-stop access to home care appointments, health monitoring, emergency response, caregiver matching, nursing services, rehabilitation, subsidy applications, and personalized care management.
